With South Africa facing a stagnant economy and widespread unemployment, Gauteng Premier David Makhura today delivered his state of the province address (Sopa), pledging to stimulate economic growth, with plans which include tapping into the potentially lucrative dagga industry. Makhura has become the second premier to show interest in cannabis, following Eastern Cape Premier Oscar Mabuyane, who has been hard at work to woo investors into the dagga-rich province. Amid loud cheers from the public gallery, Makhura was quick to explain that Gauteng planned to focus on “using dagga for medicinal use only”. “Working with the department of trade and...